		<div class="ask-content content-block">
  <div id="title" class="ask">
    <h1 class="ask">Questions about bottles</h1>
  </div>
  <div class="scroll-box">
  <div id="accordion">
    <h3>What material are made of the bottle?</h3>
    <div>
      <p>Our bottles are made of polycarbonate, a durable, chemically neutral plastic. Polycarbonate does not interact with the water, so it does not affect on it’schemical and taste properties.</p>    </div>
    <h3>How long a bottle can be used?</h3>
    <div class="box-with-scroll">
      <div class="scroll-track"></div>
      <div class="scroll-button"></div>
      <div class="text-for-scroll">
        <p>On the recommendations of productors of bottles, in the absence of mechanical damage and maintaining the appropriate appearance of a bottle it can be used about 60 times - it is about 2 years. But this applies only to polycarbonate bottles. We draw the attention of customers to the fact that not all providers use these bottles, someof them pour water in cheaper PET-bottles. At first look, the two bottles look the same. But between using polycarbonate bottles and PET-bottles, there is one significant difference. If the first  look takes the hot washing up to 60 degrees (which is an important condition of quality of the production process), the anothercan be only washed with cold water, because they melt and lose their shape from the hot water. Even more, because of its fragility PET bottles are much smaller than polycarbonate. The material of construction of the bottle is always indicated at the bottom of the bottle. The company "Чистовъ" never uses PET bottles for filling it’s water. </p>      </div>
    </div>
    <h3>How prepared bottles before bottling water?</h3>
    <div class="box-with-scroll">
      <div class="scroll-track"></div>
      <div class="scroll-button"></div>
      <div class="text-for-scroll">
        <p>All the bottles that have been returned to our factory from customers have major processing before again being filled with water and transferred to the delivery. First, we remove them from the old cover, check for the presence of visible external damages, rejectworned and old bottles, which have lost their marketability. Thereafter the bottles fall onto a conveyorwhere firstly tested automatically check for the presence of microcracks, which are not visible to the eye. Such testing is necessary in order to minimize the chance of leakage of the bottle in the future. Then each bottle passes alkaline wash solution, acidic disinfecting solution and rinsing product (pure ozone water). It should be noted that our entire production process, including the process of washing bottles, is recorded in the quality control system ISO 9001: 2000, which guarantees 100% compliance with all the rules of this process for each bottle, leaving from our conveyor.</p>      </div>
    </div>
    <h3>What is the difference between bottles with handles and bottles without handles?</h3>
    <div>
        <p>For the customer is by the only presence or absence of handles. The volume of water contained in the bottles of each type, exactly the same (5 gallons or 18.9 liters). We try to make our turnover was dominated by bottles with handles, because it is more convenient for the customer</p>    </div>
    <h3>We‘ve got a not full bottle, why?</h3>
    <div class="box-with-scroll">
      <div class="scroll-track"></div>
      <div class="scroll-button"></div>
      <div class="text-for-scroll">
        <p>The reasons may be different. With the conveyor of bottle-washing machines all bottles are filled and there is also a visual inspection of them. The leakage can be during delivery through microcracks in the bottles, which are caused by the blows of the various objects, especially sharp corners, when carrying. Normally it can be seamlessly and appears when you click on the bottle, shaking, or with temperature changes. In some cases, it may be flowing through the cover, which manifested a hidden defect, invisible during sealing. This bottle can not in any case be put on the cooler, as in an inverted bottle should be kept vacuum. If not, then there is nothing to hold water in the bottle, it starts overflowing cooler tanks and very quickly all the contents of the bottle is poured on the floor.</p>      </div>
    </div>
    <h3>What is film and why is it necessary?</h3>
    <div class="box-with-scroll">
      <div class="scroll-track"></div>
      <div class="scroll-button"></div>
      <div class="text-for-scroll">
        <p>Thermo is a protective film that covers the neck of the bottle. It serves as a guarantee of the product's originality and anti-counterfeiting. Another function of film - more hygienic protection of the bottle neck (the neck of the bottle gets less dust, the driver does not touch it by his hands during  delivery). The footage shows our trademark (logo are many CW). It has been put on each bottle automatically at the end of the manufacturing process. The absence on the delivered bottles of film should serve as an occasion for the customer to contact us and request a free changing of product.</p>      </div>
    </div>
    <h3>Why do covers have different colors?</h3>
    <div>
        <p>The colour of cover is the one of the ways to quickly distinguish which type of water is poured into the bottle:</p><p>Blue - regular water</p><p>White - fluorine</p><p>Yellow - iodine</p>    </div>
    <h3>How to remove the cover?</h3>
    <div>
        <p>Remove the shrink film, tearing it from the top, pulling the red bar. Pull the tab on the bottom of the plug, tore it by the  extruded contour to the top of the thickened part of the plug. Grasping the ruptured part of the plug, pull the plug up to the full withdrawal.</p>    </div>
    <h3>The sizes of the bottle</h3>
    <div>
        <p>Diameter 27cm</p><p>Height (with the neck) 49cm, after installation on the cooler - 40 cm</p><p>Empty weight is about 800 grams.</p>    </div>

      <input type="button" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#modal-ask" data-dismiss="modal" class="blue-btn ask-end" value="Ask your question"  />

  </div>

  </div>
